input_str: By now, we’ve all seen Twitter Bootstrap – it’s a great CSS and Javascript library open sourced by Twitter that makes it easy to produce a very polished looking site, with fantastic support for layout, navigation, typography, and much more. Twitter Bootstrap is based on Less.js, the popular dynamic CSS scripting language written by Alexis Sellier or @cloudhead. Less.js, like Node.js, is implemented completely with Javascript.
